- "sailed above the average bot detection threshold" refers to having a bot_score_english higher than the average of all bot_score_english values;
- "English waters" is a metaphorical reference to the English version of bot detection scores;
- "share the same sea age" implies users having the same age;
- "not the same vessel" signifies that the user IDs should not match, indicating they are different users;
- "travelers" and "sailed" are used metaphorically to refer to users and their performance in the system.

sql:
SELECT user_id, feedback_text, feedback_rating
FROM user_feedback
WHERE status = 'open' AND feedback_rating > 3;

SELECT notification_frequency, COUNT(*) AS musician_count
FROM user_preferences
GROUP BY notification_frequency;

SELECT user_id, AVG(bot_score_english) AS average_bot_score_english
FROM bot_detection_metrics
GROUP BY user_id;

SELECT bot_score_english, COUNT(user_id) AS user_count
FROM bot_detection_metrics
GROUP BY bot_score_english;

